                                    Lab 9 – Shortest Paths.

Problem . Implement the Dijkstra’s algorithm to find the shortest path from a source vertex ‘s’ to all
other vertices in a undirected weighted graph G.

Problem 2. Implement the Bellman-Ford algorithm to find the shortest path from a source vertex ‘s’
to all other vertices in a undirected weighted graph G. Your program will need to detect if there is a
cycle of negative weight; Print a message if this occurs.

Problem 3. Implement Johnson’s algorithm to find the shortest path between all pairs of vertices in
a graph. You can read about Johnson’s algorithm here. http://www.geeksforgeeks.org/johnsons-algorithm

